<TITLE> UNO cancels freedom fighters' reception in Tangail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, Apr 14 (bdnews24.com) - Local authorities halted a reception ceremony for freedom fighters, and a handicapped gold medalist of the Paralympics, Monday in Madhupur, Tangail, said reception organisers. Madhupur Nagorik Forum organiser Faruk Hosain, secretary Mizanur Rahman and other forum members told a press conference the ceremony was scheduled to be held at Madhupur Monday evening. But they said the Upazila Nirbahi Officer cancelled the programme, saying that there had been discrepancies between the invitation letters and the original application by the organisers. Sector Commanders Forum president retired air vice marshal AK Khondokar was invited as chief guest. The Madhupur Nagorik Forum organised a discussion meting to replace the cancelled programme. The sector commander joined the discussion. The organisers said the upazila authorities had originally given written permission on Mar 31for the programme to go ahead. bdnews2
